text: Marine Science Magnet High School of Southeastern Connecticut is a public high school in Groton, Connecticut, in the United States. It opened on September 1, 2011. In the academic year 2012–2013 there were 178 students enrolled in grades 9–11, of which 94 were male and 84 female. Approximately 93% were ethnically white, and 7% Hispanic. ==Notes== Category:Buildings and structures in Groton, Connecticut Category:Schools in New London County, Connecticut Category:Public high schools in Connecticut Category:Educational institutions established in 1928
